  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;COMPLAINT...&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Having waited just over 3 months for an appointment, I arrived at the department early today to be told that the clinic had been cancelled as the consultant had broken down! Apparently, I had been telephoned (but my phone was off as would already have been in the hospital, having arrived early in order to park and not be late for my 8.30am appointment). At this stage, I asked to speak to someone in charge and was told that nobody was available?!

I waited a further 1.5 hours in the hope that I could be seen by another doctor (there were other Rheumatology Doctors working in the clinic), only to be told that nobody was available to see me.

Surely, some kind of &quot;contingency plan&quot; needs to be in place within the department to overcome such an issue ever happening again. I actually offered to personally collect the Doctor who had broken down but was informed that she wouldn't be coming in as she didn't have an afternoon clinic, so at that stage felt like my own Morning appointment just didn't matter.

I have had to re-arrange several things in order to attend today's appointment and will do the same when  I am given a new appointment - so the inconvenience to me is HUGE...and I find it insulting to have received several text message reminders about my appointment, telling me how &quot;missed appointments&quot; cost the NHS X amount of pounds...only to arrive and be let down so badly by Russells Hall Hospital...&lt;/CommentText&gt;
